reference "tab:MC_Undoped_QW_Extracted_Parameters_Manual_Couples_Oscillator"

\end_inset

 together with a list of manually obtained energetic locations of these
 resonances.
 The fitting curves lie very close to the calculated anti-crossing data.
 The fitting model energy parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{X}$
\end_inset

 values are almost identical to the manually obtained values and the fitted
 coupling constant, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hbar\Omega_{X}$
\end_inset

, reflect the coupling strength in the interaction regions between the photon
 and the excitonic fields, and their size is in direct correlation to the
 observed splitting between adjacent branches of the anti-crossing dispersion
 curves.
 Using this data we can also convince ourselves that the strong interaction
 condition, namely that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hbar\Omega_{X}>\gamma_{X},\,\gamma_{C}$
\end_inset

, is satisfied for each one of the polaritonic branches.
